Key Match Events: Bas de Leede picked up 4-62 with his seam bowling to bowl out Pakistan for 286
Haris Rauf claimed 3-43, Shaheen Afridi claimed 1-37, and Hasan Ali bagged 2-37
Vikramjit Singh made a fighting 52 off 67 balls and combined in a 70-run stand with de Leede
Rauf took the sting out of the Netherlands' chase, claiming the wickets of Teja Nidamanuru and Scott Edwards in quick succession
Logan van Beek made an unbeaten run-a-ball 28 to narrow the margin of defeat
Post-Match Reflections: Babar Azam credited the bowlers for their performance and praised the batting efforts of Rizwan and Shakeel
Scott Edwards thought the total was a par one and felt the Netherlands performed well in the chase
Miscellaneous Highlights: Pakistan beat the Netherlands by 81 runs
